<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I feel your pain, I played a mage when the game was first released some 5 years back.  I gave up on the mage class, everything you said is right on the mark.  From the start of the game till now necros have made out like bandits, wizards have done great, druid stayed about the same, enchanters have done great, clerics have done ok. But mages never went anywhere.  For along time I called them the forgotten class.  I think verant sees balance in how many ppl play a class.  Example when first released No one wanted to play a necromancer, all the crying was they cant do anything bla bla bla.  Now I look at what they can do and I say wow, and lots of ppl play them now. Then look at druids, ya they were strong all classes complained about them and lots of ppl played them now dots do 60% damage and so on an so on.  And it’s the same with all classes, for a time the hybrids numbers were dropping off, the experience penalty was to high a price ppl thought, so they got rid of it, or reduced it so much you cant tell there is one.  Humans were to gain experience the fastest out of all the races, hardly anyone played halflings and now they get the experience bonus.  Well all this leads to DON’T PLAY THE MAGE CLASS!   If the number of mages drop in the game to almost nothing I bet you will see verant say hmmmm  not balanced anymore better pump em up some.  Think of it like a boycott.  I tried this once but maby it was to early. I would try again but I think im done with eq.  Planet side has my eye now =)
