At first, i read over your post and agreed with you, but then i thought about it and i really don't agree with any of that, i'll try to explain why, i apologize in advance for any sarcasm i may use, but its late and sarcasm is fun  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">, its not meant to be mean.<P>Nukes: Wizards do not have a pet, thus their nukes are the strongest. Druids do not have a pet, thus their nukes are second strongest. You have a pet, yet you want your nukes to be stronger than a druids.<P>Pets:<P>In response to the wizards getting a pet, i can't answer that yet, but it will probably just be something that focuses their spells and adds damage, obviously not a full on pet and nothing that would make their pet + spells more powerful than yours. You say you should get the familiar as well or no one should get it? But you are already stronger than them, even if they have the familiar and you don't, why should you get it? Beastlords do get a pet, you have no idea how strong it is, they're just creating another pet class, how are you mad over another pet class? What if the pet is nowhere near as strong as yours, and their melee skills are bad, how strong is this complaint then? If you're mad over a class you know nothing about then you need to learn patience to wait until they are made.<P>Mana-Regen: Yes, you not getting a form of mana-regen does suck, you're going to be sitting down a lot longer, but you do get the mod-rod. I think you're missing the best aspect of a mod rod. The mod rod wasn't made to increase mana regen, but to get you out of a bad situation. If that creature is about to die, your pet is about to die, and you are oom, you know what a chanter does? runs, druid? runs, shaman? runs, necro? runs, mage? mod rod and nuke him = you win. Perhaps you feel that is an unfair trade, apparently verant doesn't.<P>Escape: Mod rod falls into this category, maybe it will let you cast that last pet so you can run to the zone, maybe it will let you zone, but it eliminates the need for escape. Otherwise, what is so bad about gate? As an enchanter, if i'm caught in a bad situation, i'm probably just going to mezz and gate, or mezz and zone, so what's the difference between mezzing and gating or just gating?<P>Spells: You think other classes get much more than trinket spells aside from their main lines?<P>Beastlord: Yes they get a pet, can ch it, and can zone with it. You know nothing about the class at this point, if you're jealous already i can't wait to see your reaction when you find out what they actually do. As for why they didn't let you zone with your pets, i dunno maybe verant just didn't think you were special enough, who knows, its not like its a really big deal, its just a convenience, its like enchanters who are hung up on illusion spectre, who cares.<P>My overall review: You are asking for everything. You want to not have the third best nukes, but the second or first. You have to have the best pet hands down, and be able to ch it, no other classes are allowed to do anything you are not allowed to do with your pets of course. Just think how crazy some of those things are. If your nukes were on par with a wizard, what the hell would be the point of the entire wizard class. Aww, you can't quad kite, i feel sorry for you... really i do... And another thing, most of those classes you mention get the mana regen affects at very high levels, upper 50's, what the hell good do they do then? you think a lvl 60 runs around soloing stuff? hell no he's on raids, lvl 59's don't go exping, they go raiding, as do most people with the capability to mana regen themselves except enchanters, necros, and shaman, that's three classes, not just about every other class. And the reason mages were not given root was because the strength of their pet warrented the loss of root... are you trying to tell me your pet isn't strong enough? strong enough in comparison to what? it alone can out melee any other class, what do you want? Lastly, you complain that your class is not balanced. Name one other class that you feel is better than you, and for what reason? IMHO, mages are overbalanced. and they gave you coth and an anti-summoning spell. you should go to the enchanter board, read up for a little bit. You know what we got at high levels, jack ****, we have absolutely nothing, we have next to 0 benefit to a group, but we don't complain, we find ways around it. Some of us give up and quit, some of us find things that are fun. At least you'll always have a pet, no matter what happens you're a large benefit to a group/raid, while many other classes fade out and become useless.<P>Damn, this thing must be pretty long. I was just writing a paper so i'm in the elaborating mood, oh well, hope you read it over and consider what i said. If you disagree with anything, let me know why, but from my perspective you didn't really back yourself up at all. (this is a rant, if you just wanted to rant i'm not trying to stop you, just if you were interested its my opinion on it).
