Well Aeristotle, I have played a druid to 53, and I currently have a lvl 48 magi. I thought it was common knowledge that Magicians were the third best nukers at high lvls. Around 34 or so, I think we are actually second, but that changes a tad higher up. Druids first mana regen is at lvl 54, and it is a wolfform. Although Druids get some very decent nukes and DoTs, every time I have grouped with my druid I usually end up being the primary or secondary healer + evac + minor buffer. Healing is a much better use of your mana than landing that starfire when you are a druid, and usually aren't much of a damage class when grouped. <P>I'm personally quite happy with my role of group damage dealer however (as magi of course). The two other classes most comparable to the magi, are the wizard and the rogue (maybe ranger, but they never seem to put out insane damage like the other two classes). In an exp group, I almost always do more damage than the other two classes, that in itself is validation for playing a magi. <P>Rogues are preferable for raids because they don't follow that crazy pathing verant blessed our pets with, and they don't get resisted. Much like a magi, they allow a group to kill things much faster, but in even a chainpulling group, a magi with a non-suckfest pet (not earth   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> )can do more dmg.<P>I personally believe that wizards are a very underpowered class. They are more usful on a raid if the leader won't allow you to use your pet (which is quite possibly your own fault for not exercising good pet control in the past) only because they have a line of spells with a much lower resist rate. <P>In any exp group the magi seems to have a distinct advantage. Magicians are an asset to have in any exp group, not to mention a whole lot of fun to play    <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"> . I kinda forgot what the topic was, uh, but I think I was trying to point out that mages are a very useful class    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
