 - One's a cleric hybrid (mostly defensive), one's a necro hybrid (mostly offensive with a few clerical spells thrown in (Lifetaps)  Thx again VI!  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> ) <P>Enchanters - Mana givers, mezzers, cast the third (I believe) most powerful pet in the game.  Oh yah, forgot about charmers also.  <P>Bards - I don't know what the hell to call these things, an annoyance is what I call them.   <P>Monks - Damage dealers, can FD, and Mend.  <P>Clerics - Healers.  <BR>Rogues - damage dealers when they backstab, dual weild, dual attack, sneak, hide, safe fall, evade, and instill doubt.  <P>Mages.  Can summon the master pet, and are the master of damage shields.<P>K.   I don't think that in my 50+ days, I've had a mob with under 5K of hp.  Now, this might sound great to all you newbie mages out there, but it's not.  Let's first of all start with how much my pet does in damage, VS. how much said mob does in damage.   My pet is hitting it for 55 max.  My earth pet (lvl 51) has around 2600 hp.  Now let's take a look at what said mob does.  Said mob does 100+ (sometimes 200+) and as stated above, has around 5K (minimum) hitpoints.  <P>Doesn't take a genious to figure out that with my most powerful damage shield ( 25 hp of damage), said mob will win.  Plus this acts as a taunt, and causes said mob to hit for max each time, causing my pet to go down even faster.<P>But alas, this counts us out of the equation.    My most powerful nuke, lava bolt, does 810 points of damage to said mob (barring resists and such).  Yes, there is some debate over whether or not to let your pet taunt two-three times before standing up and nuking.  BUT, alas, when I have done this, I usually find my pet with next to no hp, or no hp at all.  When I have stood up and nuked right away, no problem, pet always comes back to me with about 25% - 50% hp.  But, again, this draws aggro.  On three, out of the four pets that we get, they DO NOT have root or the firepower to taunt the thing off yer arse when you've just pumped your third lava bolt into it.   Mages get two earth pets 50+, and plus the hardest epic in the blasted game.  <BR>Gee, thanks VI, for makes mages everywhere $%&^ in one hand, wish in other.   Have crap being summoned in one hand, have a pet they can't heal in the other.   Make up your mind.   <P>Are we a pet class, or are we a summoners class?<P>And you wonder why we're steamed?  Heh.  Take a look at those BLord pet buffs again, take a look at the number of spells that they can cast on the pet beside their regular buffs, take a look at how they can zone with their pets (and no, it's not the cost of malachite as one person put it, it's the mob waiting just on the other side of zone line and that 10 second cast time that scares the bejeezus out of me), and take a look at their stats.  It doesn't matter if they only max at 100.  All that VI'll do is come up with new and more uber weapons than they already have!  Thus increasing the damage output of the beastlord.  Ahhh, yeh, and I know this definately compares with old Jobober quading for 55, while he's getting the snot pounded out of him by quad 100's.  <P><BR>K, I think I'm done here<P>--------------------<P>A wyvern in CS? An eighth of blue, solo.<P>Spider in Velk's? Half a blue, solo.<P>52nd level magician without his pet getting beaten down by a tizmak which is 25-30 levels below him? Priceless.<P>There are times when a magician is useful. But for all other times there's a magician at 52nd level saying, "Beat this thing off me so I can get my pet up!"<P>VI. The Official Magician Haters. Accepted Everywhere. Even WotC. Laughing at Magicians because they are so weak since 1999.
